WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.480
There are so many new things coming from the R open source community every day. It will

00:00:12.480 --> 00:00:20.639
be really hard to follow the latest news about R. R has come to define a magical data science

00:00:20.639 --> 00:00:27.719
programming language. To build on this, R Weekly team set out to create an ultimate

00:00:27.719 --> 00:00:36.639
real-time reading experience for the R community. R Weekly will help you learn R every week.

00:00:36.639 --> 00:00:42.880
Every aspect has been designed for a clean and comfortable reading experience. Every

00:00:42.880 --> 00:00:50.119
Monday, R Weekly editor will aggregate all of the great sources from the community and

00:00:50.119 --> 00:00:57.959
create a clear and simple newsletter for you. You can visit R Weekly website to read

00:00:57.959 --> 00:01:06.519
the latest and history issues. There are also email subscription and RSS feed. Choose your

00:01:06.519 --> 00:01:13.959
favorite way to enjoy the content from the entire R universe. R Weekly has a wide range

00:01:13.959 --> 00:01:22.360
of content with a comfortable and clear user interface. Weekly editor's picks deliver

00:01:22.360 --> 00:01:29.480
high-quality articles for you to learn the best practices and boost your R knowledge.

00:01:29.480 --> 00:01:37.440
There is also a podcast. It contains the weekly highlights about the community. This component

00:01:37.440 --> 00:01:45.440
works in harmony to maintain an exceptional reading and listening experience.

00:01:45.440 --> 00:01:53.040
How to contribute to R Weekly? The editing process is fully open source on

00:01:53.040 --> 00:02:01.800
GitHub. Contributing to R Weekly is as easy as editing in a text editor. Click the edit

00:02:01.800 --> 00:02:08.199
button and create a pull request and you will be able to show your content to thousands

00:02:08.199 --> 00:02:15.440
of users every week. If you do not have a GitHub account, you can also use the submit

00:02:15.440 --> 00:02:24.919
page. The submit page is in the header of R Weekly website. Type your link in the form

00:02:24.919 --> 00:02:30.679
and R Weekly team member will see your link and review your content.

00:02:30.679 --> 00:02:37.880
How to become an R Weekly team member? Please create several pull requests on GitHub to

00:02:37.880 --> 00:02:47.399
get familiar with the process to edit a newsletter. And then take the R Weekly contributing survey.

00:02:47.880 --> 00:02:54.919
We will reach out to you very soon. Here are some small tips and tricks you can do with

00:02:54.919 --> 00:03:03.639
R Weekly website. You can filter the links with the filter box. For example, search Shiny.

00:03:03.639 --> 00:03:11.000
You can search all of the links in the R Weekly website from the search box or from GitHub.

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:14.839
For example, you can search ggplot2 and tidy text.

00:03:17.800 --> 00:03:24.039
When you hover on some links, we will show you the preview of the content and you will

00:03:24.039 --> 00:03:30.360
be able to know what you will read in the links. You can turn on night mode.

00:03:32.839 --> 00:03:40.360
I want to say all of the R Weekly team members, they have done a really good job on this project

00:03:40.360 --> 00:03:49.399
and all of our communication is remote and over Slack. I want to say all of R Weekly patrons,

00:03:49.399 --> 00:03:53.639
they have been supporting this project for a very long time.

00:03:55.800 --> 00:04:06.199
Hope you will enjoy the R Weekly project and see you every Monday.

